devdoc.details: Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to specific functions. By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This can later be changed with {transferOwnership}. This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

IEACAggregatorProxy rewardOracle: The Price Oracle of a reward to visualize the incentives at the UI Frontend.                                     Must follow Chainlink Aggregator IEACAggregatorProxy interface to be compatible.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.reward: The reward token that incentives the asset

setEmissionAdmin(address,address).details: Updates the admin of the reward emissionOnly callable by the owner of the EmissionManager

userdoc.notice: It manages the list of admins of reward emissions and provides functions to control reward emissions.

params.reward: The address of the rewarding token

params.config: The assets configuration input, the list of structs contains the following fields:   uint104 emissionPerSecond: The emission per second following rewards unit decimals.   uint256 totalSupply: The total supply of the asset to incentivize   uint40 distributionEnd: The end of the distribution of the incentives for an asset   address asset: The asset address to incentivize   address reward: The reward token address   ITransferStrategy transferStrategy: The TransferStrategy address with the install hook and claim logic. params.asset: The address of the incentivized asset
params.assetIndex: The index of the asset distribution
params.newDistributionEnd: The new end timestamp of the reward distribution
params.newEmission: The new emissions per second value of the reward distribution
params.oldDistributionEnd: The old end timestamp of the reward distribution
params.oldEmission: The old emissions per second value of the reward distribution
params.reward: The address of the reward token

params.reward: The address of the token reward
The address of the token reward is claimed
params.to: The address of the receiver of the rewards
params.user: The address of the user rewards has been claimed on behalf of

EMISSION_MANAGER().details: Returns the address of the emission manager

returns._0: The address of the EmissionManager

claimAllRewards(address[],address).details: Claims all rewards for a user to the desired address, on all the assets of the pool, accumulating the pending rewards

params.assets: The list of assets to check eligible distributions before claiming rewards
params.to: The address that will be receiving the rewards

@dev Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where
 there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to
 specific functions.
 By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This
 can later be changed with {transferOwnership}.
 This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier
 `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to
 the owner.
@dev Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.
@dev Returns the address of the current owner.

 `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.
